<sn><md>### Course Contents

| Topic                                      | Details                                                                                                                                                                                                         |
| ------------------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Soil Quality Concept**                   | Physical, chemical, and biological indicators<br>importance of soil quality<br>assessment<br>how earthworm populations can be improved<br>importance of monitoring changes                                      |
| **Environmental Quality**                  | Modern concepts<br>legal aspects<br>environmental rights and issues<br>standards, pollution, and contamination<br>remediation of soil from inorganic and organic contaminants                                   |
| **Sustainable Land and Forest Management** | Concepts<br>land resources of Bangladesh<br>land degradation causes and effects<br>strategies for sustainable management<br>ecosystem services provided by forests<br>objectives of forest soil management      |
| **Water Quality**                          | Definition<br>parameters and requirements<br>standards and classification<br>physical and chemical processes in surface water<br>soil–water interactions<br>monitoring and purification processes               |
| **Air Quality**                            | Definition<br>standard setting process<br>classification of air pollutants<br>ambient air<br>sources and effects of air pollution<br>AQI in Bangladesh<br>global policies on ozone depletion and climate change |
</md></sn><sn><md>### Recommended Readings

* Fundamentals of Environmental Studies
* Environmental Chemistry
* Ambient Air Quality in Bangladesh
* A Handbook on Analyses of Soil, Plant and Water</md></sn><sn></sn>